  Introduction    PURPOSE: Lead complex and non-recurring special projects, initiatives and teams. Deliver technical leadership, process and design standardization, and peer development across NiSource engineering. This effort supplements engineering managers and leaders as a leadership resource with responsibilities beyond the expected capabilities of a senior engineer, including professional review, oversight, and certification of engineering designs.  The principal engineer will also evaluate, design, and estimate natural gas distribution facilities for new business, public and system improvement, and maintenance projects according to company standards and other applicable guidelines and codes. Natural gas distribution facilities may consist of main lines, service lines, and measurement & regulation equipment. The principal engineer will provide technical assistance and support for Construction and Field Operations staff involved in the construction, operation, and maintenance of distribution facilities. Collaborate and coordinate efforts with key stakeholders on large distribution projects.  (Note: P.E. license requirements apply to those entering the Principal Engineer role as of 5/11/2019)  KEY RESULTS:    Well executed special projects and initiatives   P.E. stamped projects   Technically strong engineering team members   Consistent results in design, planning and close-out processes across NGD   Ensure safe and reliable delivery of energy services at best cost   Meet or exceed internal/external customer expectations   Actual project costs are within 10% of estimated costs   Safe/efficient high quality engineering designs that comply with policies, practices, standards, and applicable codes   Productivity and performance results that meet or exceed expectations   Timely delivery of all facility designs   Consistent communication with key stakeholders and business partners   Ensure post and pre winter operation system reviews are held      Responsibilities      Perform project manager responsibilities for special projects and initiatives   Exercise responsible charge over projects being designed by other engineers   P.E. stamp project designs under principal engineers responsible charge according to state requirements   Conduct QA/QC and follow-up development for engineering activities   Represent engineering for development of process, material and gas standards   Supplement engineering leadership and serve in an engineering leader role on an interim basis as need.   Evaluate, design, and estimate natural gas distribution facilities   Prepare permit applications and easement requests   Prepare detailed drawings   Compile capital work order / job order packets   Prepare budget estimates   Report on project variances   Support Operations employees in emergency situations   Provide training and guidance to new personnel   Act as liaison to state, county, and local government officials   Conduct winter preparedness reviews   Assist in contract bid documentation   Maintain MAOP documentation   Review and process completion reports and 'as-built' drawings   Maintain professional license / registration in good standing      Qualifications    Key Work Experiences/Education: Required for Selection:    5 years of related engineering experience   Professional Engineering license in state being supported   Demonstrated expertise and capabilities in project management   Experience and knowledge that meets the requirements as set forth in the engineering advancement criteria   Knowledge of company and industry codes, rules, regulations, standards, policies, and procedures   Bachelors degree in an engineering curriculum from an EAC/ABET accredited college or university.   Strong communication and interpersonal skills   Preferred for Selection:    10 years of gas distribution experience   5 years of gas distribution engineering experience   Professional Engineering license in multiple NiSource states   Masters degree in Business or Engineering   Technical/Functional Competencies: Required for Selection:    Demonstrated knowledge of various pc applications and software (i.e. Word, Excel, AutoCAD)   Preferred for Selection:    Demonstrated knowledge of technical business applications and systems used by NGD engineering (e.g. Work Management Systems, Synergee, AutoCad; GIS; GasCalc; Pipeline ToolBox   General Competencies: Required for Selection:    Coaching   Developing Others   Building a Successful Team   Building Strategic Working Relationships   Building Partnerships   Communication   Collaboration   Building Trust   Leading Through Vision & Values   Adaptability   Facilitating Change   Continuous Improvement   Continuous Learning   Decision Making   Quality Orientation   Planning and Organizing      Inclusion & Diversity    Value inclusion within your day to day responsibilities by respecting others' perspectives/convictions, engaging others' opinions, creating a safe environment where people, ideas, and opinions are valued within your Team/Customers and external partners. column4:
['
Job Title:\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 SAP CELONIS Solution Architect (NAVSUP IBM)Job Code:\xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa012080495Job Location:\xa0 \xa0 \xa0 Mechanicsburg, Pennsylvania​Imagine One Technology & Management, Ltd., is currently seeking SAP CELONIS Solution Architect “contingent” on approval of candidates by the prime contractor and/or government client. This position supports the US Navy in Mechanicsburg, Pennsylvania, but has the potential for remote support. As a SAP CELONIS Solution Architect, responsibilities will include, but are not limited to the following:\xa0\xa0
Applying expertise/capabilities to lead implementation of Solution Manager for IT and Business Process Monitoring.
Crafting SAP Solution Landscapes.
Providing assistance on Landscape growth assessment.
Establishing standards and thresholds for monitoring and auditing to ensure stable and supportable reporting implementation and continual requested capabilities.
Driving service improvements and efficiencies through the design and development of effective automation.
Participating and collaborating with other operations teams to provide root-cause analysis for all client outages and failed changes in the environment.
\xa0Experience Requirements: \xa0\xa0
Five (5) years of experience in SAP or other ERP equivalent COTS.\xa0\xa0
Thorough knowledge in SAP Infrastructure with emphasis on SAP Basis, Security, Change management, SAP Integration technologies, Development Workbench, Memory management, and Workload management within SAP CCMS.
Well-versed with SAP Data Dictionary, SAP Solution Manager, Transport management and Oracle physical design for SAP.\xa0
Knowledgeable with the HP-UX UNIX, Oracle RDBMS and Windows 2000 and 2003 platforms.\xa0
Knowledgeable in Web Infrastructure, SAP Integration Layers and NetWeaver Architecture.\xa0
Experience in SAP Sizing, Workload characterization and Capacity Planning.\xa0
Strong communication skills both oral and written, with all levels of the organization.\xa0
Excellent teamwork skills, including working with internal and external departments and organizations; Experience with virtual, cross-functional teams with track record of delivering results.
DoD experience preferred.
\xa0\xa0Educational Requirements:\xa0\xa0Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related field.An additional two years of relevant experience may be substituted for the Bachelor’s degree.\xa0Security Requirements: \xa0\xa0
U.S. Citizenship required
Active DoD Security Clearance
\xa0Imagine One offers a full package of benefits and competitive salary. Excellent group medical, vision and dental programs. 401K savings plan; $4K annual tuition reimbursement ($5K if pursuing Master’s degree); employee training, development and education programs; profit sharing; advancement opportunities; and much more!\xa0\xa0*Imagine One “Contingent” offers for employment may stipulate that one or more requirements be satisfied before final commitment between candidate and Imagine One is established; namely, award of contract to the Imagine One Team.\xa0 Contingent requirements vary and mayalso include, but not be limited to additional factors (i.e., the position still being available after negotiations with the Government; final approval of your qualifications by the Government; or ability to successfully acquire and/or transfer a DoD security clearance).
\xa0

Recommended skills

Architecture
Sap Erp
Data Dictionary
Sap Solution Manager
Transport Management Systems

column4:
['
Location:  Shiremanstown, PA
Description:  Our client is currently seeking a Scrum Master\xa0\xa0The Scrum Master will help educate the team in Scrum, Extreme, Programming (XP), Kanban, and SAFe, ensuring that the agreed upon Agile process is being followed. The Scrum Master’s primary responsibility is assisting the self-organizing, self-managing team achieve its goals by teaching and coaching team practices, implementing and supporting SAFe principles and practices, identifying and eliminating impediments, facilitating flow, and coordinating activities with other teams. Facilitate Agile Release Train (ART) events and processes and assist the teams in delivering value across the organization by providing the planning, directing, controlling, and implementing of moderate to complex projects. This job will have the following responsibilities:  

Support the product owners to ensure the team is aligned to strategic roadmaps, strategies, and objectives while facilitating a healthy team dynamic with respect to the priorities and scope.
Eliminate impediments by actively addressing blocking issues that are beyond the team’s authority or may require support from other teams so that the team can remain focused on achieving the objectives of the Iteration.
Facilitate creation of and support team rules.
Collaborate with Release Train Engineer to coordinate inter-team cooperation and help keep the train operations well.
Guide, coach and motivate the team with the goal of increasing productivity.
Facilitate the resolution of interpersonal conflicts, challenges, and opportunities for growth, escalating problems to management where necessary, but only after internal team processes have failed to resolve the issue
Help individuals and teams through personnel changes.
Support Program Increment Planning activities and cross team dependencies and acceptance of an approved
Program Increment Plan.
Monitor the team’s schedule ensuring stories are completed on time and accepted as done by the Product
Owner.
Facilitate team SAFe ceremonies (Daily Stand ups, Sprint Review, Backlog Refinement, Sprint Retro, and Sprint Planning).
Support cross team collaboration to manage value stream dependencies.
Prepare and present reports/boards on progress and success of sprints, Program Increments (PI).
Communicate with product and technical managers on sprint and PI status.
Communicate with management and outside stakeholders; help protect the team from uncontrolled expansion of work.
Accountable for ensuring SAFe methodology is used by the team.
Identify and manage project risks. Develop mitigation strategies and recommendations to avoid possible impacts to a project.

                        Qualifications & Requirements: 

Demonstrated analytical, problem solving, critical thinking, organizational, and project management skills with the ability to focus attention on details.
Exhibit Lean Agile Leadership, exhibit the behaviors of a Lean-Agile Leader, help the team embrace SAFe Core
Values, adopt and apply SAFe Principles, and implement SAFe Practices.
Demonstrated ability to foster team collaboration and empowerment.
Ability to assess and identify dependencies and actions needed to successfully perform work through various teams.
Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively and with little supervision to resolve problems professionally and promptly.
Ability to think strategically and understand the key business problems client is trying to solve.
Demonstrated experience with SAFe and/or other Agile Software Development methodologies and tools.
Understand the Agency business model, business strategy, business processes and operations.
Ability to manage ambiguity and undertake forward planning.
Strong communication skills; both written and verbal.
Excellent interpersonal skills with the ability to interact professionally with all levels within the organization

column4: ['Position SummaryReporting to the Test Engineering Manager, the Test Engineer develops, qualifies, and documents test processes for electronic assemblies and systems to ensure internal quality standards are met and maintained. This position is responsible to ensure test processes are capable, reliable, and optimal.', 'The Test Engineer must be able to lead Test Engineering Technicians through continuous improvement ideologies. This position is expected to fulfill duties and consistently find solutions to rising problems. The position requires engaging operators in conversation to investigate problems, develop a solution and independently act on resolving testing issues in the manufacturing environment. It is important that the Test Engineer understands the importance of integrity in every decision to ensure that quality is never sacrificed. All employees are expected to embrace and adhere to the Safety and Electrostatic Discharge (ESD) policies and practices.', 'Essential Job Functions:', 'Minimum Requirements:', 'Preferred Requirements• Bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering or similar disciplineSupervisory Responsibilities• TE I and II position does not have direct supervisory responsibilities; however, position is expected to work closely with and delegate work to Test Engineering Technicians and Specialists.Tools and Equipment Necessary• Magnifying devices, measuring tools, and electronic test and calibration equipment• Use of general hand toolsRequired Licenses, Certificates or Knowledge• Knowledgeable in high level software languages such as, GEOTest ATEasy, National Instruments Lab View and TestStand• Knowledgeable in analog and digital circuitry, used in industrial controls• Knowledgeable in analog calibration disciplines of electronic hardware• Proficient computer skills to include Microsoft Office (Work, Excel, PowerPoint) Sharepoint, Internet Explorer and Outlook.']

column4: ['Position Summary', 'Red Lion Controls has an opportunity for a Senior Hardware Engineering Manager to join our leadership team as a vital component to successfully achieving our aggressive business goals.\xa0 The Senior Hardware Engineering Manager will lead a talented group of hardware design engineers, to develop and design customer-focused automation & networking switch solutions.\xa0 Red Lion, known for its strong engineering and excellent product quality, has an opportunity to capture significant share gains within the exciting Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT).\xa0 Offering several attractive elements, including a knowledgeable, dedicated and talented engineering base, a well-regarded proprietary operating system, recently launched new product lines, exciting new technology, and international markets ripe for growth, Red Lion is well-positioned to offer a successful leader significant career and personal growth.', 'Red Lion has increased its focus on and desire to grow international markets therefore the opportunities are significant for those with the proper experience outside the US and a global mindset. While the initial experience will be managing a team of domestic engineers who are working on the latest NPI projects, the opportunity exists to gain exposure to diverse groups of engineers in other parts of the world.', 'The Senior Hardware Engineering Manager will be responsible for helping define and update the long-term technology roadmap of the company, shaping the development teams including organization structure, role / level definitions, and career development of hardware design engineers.\xa0 Senior Hardware Engineering Manager will collaborate with marketing to lead and drive the engineering and product teams to define, design, and scale up the cost effective manufacturing for the next generation product platforms.
